hh3cEntityExtend.description: The private MIB file includes the general extent information of the device.

Hh3cAdminState.name: Hh3cAdminState
Hh3cAdminState.description: The administrative state for this object, and it is possible to set the state when needed. A value of locked means the resource is administratively prohibited from use. A value of shuttingDown means that usage is administratively limited to current instances of use. A value of unlocked means the resource is not administratively prohibited from use.
Hh3cAdminState.reference: ITU Recommendation X.731, 'Information Technology - Open Systems Interconnection - System Management: State Management Function', 1992

Hh3cOperState.name: Hh3cOperState
Hh3cOperState.description: Represents the possible values of operational states. A value of disabled means the resource is totally inoperable. A value of enabled means the resource is partially or fully operable.
Hh3cOperState.reference: ITU Recommendation X.731, 'Information Technology - Open Systems Interconnection - System Management: State Management Function', 1992

Hh3cAlarmStatus.name: Hh3cAlarmStatus
Hh3cAlarmStatus.description: Represents the possible values of alarm status. When no bits of this attribute are set, then none of the status conditions described below are present. When the value of under repair is set, the resource is currently being repaired. When the value of critical is set, one or more critical alarms are active against the resource. When the value of major is set, one or more major alarms are active against the resource. When the value of minor is set, one or more minor alarms are active against the resource. When the value of warning is set, one or more warning alarms are active against the resource. When the value of indeterminate is set, one or more alarms of indeterminate severity are active against the resource. When the value of alarm outstanding is set, one or more alarms is active against the resource. The fault may or may not be disabling.
Hh3cAlarmStatus.reference: ITU Recommendation X.731, 'Information Technology - Open Systems Interconnection - System Management: State Management Function', 1992

Hh3cStandbyStatus.name: Hh3cStandbyStatus
Hh3cStandbyStatus.description: Represents the possible values of standby status. A value of hotStandby means the resource is not providing service, but is will be immediately able to take over the role of the resource to be backed-up, without the need for initialization activity, and will contain the same information as the resource to be backed up. A value of coldStandy means that the resource is to back-up another resource, but will not be immediately able to take over the role of a resource to be backed up, and will require some initialization activity. A value of providingService means the resource is providing service.
Hh3cStandbyStatus.reference: ITU Recommendation X.731, 'Information Technology - Open Systems Interconnection - System Management: State Management Function', 1992

hh3cEntityExtCriticalTemperatureThreshol.name: hh3cEntityExtCriticalTemperatureThreshold
hh3cEntityExtCriticalTemperatureThreshol.description: The threshold for the critical Temperature. When temperature exceeds the critical temperature, a notification will be sent.

hh3cEntityExtErrorStatus.name: hh3cEntityExtErrorStatus
hh3cEntityExtErrorStatus.description: Indicate the error state of this entity object. Now it only supports Port, general power supply, RPS power supply and board/Subcard. It may have one of these values. The following four values can be used for all kinds of entities. notSupported(1) means this entity cannot support this function. normal(2) means the statement of this entity is normal. for ports, it doesn't differentiate 10M/s, 100M/s, 1000M/s, duplex and half-duplex. For fan, power supply and board-Subcard, it means their states are normal. postFailure(3) means the entity fails to POST. entityAbsent(4) means the entity is absent now. The following values is depended on the entity. For Port entities, it may have the following values. If its POST is failure, then the value of the instance will be postFailure(3), otherwise the value will be normal(2). If enable power supply over Ethernet on this port is failure, the value of this instance will be poeError(11), otherwise it will be normal(2). For stack port, if it connects to another stack port normally, and these two units merge into one stack, then the value of this instance will be normal(2). If something wrong occurs and the unit cannot merge into stack, the value of this instance will be stackPortFailed(23). If the stack port forms resilient daisy chain with another stack port on the other unit, the value of this instance will be stackPortBlocked(22). For SFP ports, if it fail to receive, the value of this instance will be sfpRecvError(31), if it fail to send, the value is sfpSendError(32), if it fail to send and receive, the value is sfpBothError(33), otherwise it will be normal(2). fanError(41) means that the fan stops working. psuError(51) means that the Power Supply Unit is in the state of fault. rpsError(61) means the RPS is in the state of fault. moduleFaulty(71) means the Module is in the state of fault. sensorError(81) means the sensor is in the state of fault. hardwareFaulty(91) means the hardware of specified entity is in the state of fault. NMS must be compatible with the states which may be added in the future.

hh3cEntityExtPhyMemSize.name: hh3cEntityExtPhyMemSize
hh3cEntityExtPhyMemSize.description: The memory size of entity. This is the physical attribute of entity.

hh3cEntityExtPhyCpuFrequency.name: hh3cEntityExtPhyCpuFrequency
hh3cEntityExtPhyCpuFrequency.description: The CPU frequency of entity. Unit of measure is MHZ.

hh3cEntityExtFirstUsedDate.name: hh3cEntityExtFirstUsedDate
hh3cEntityExtFirstUsedDate.description: The first used date of the entity.

hh3cEntityExtCpuAvgUsage.name: hh3cEntityExtCpuAvgUsage
hh3cEntityExtCpuAvgUsage.description: The average CPU usage for the entity in a period of time.

hh3cEntityExtMemAvgUsage.name: hh3cEntityExtMemAvgUsage
hh3cEntityExtMemAvgUsage.description: The average memory usage for the entity in a period of time.

hh3cEntityExtCriticalLowerTemperatureThr.name: hh3cEntityExtCriticalLowerTemperatureThreshold
hh3cEntityExtCriticalLowerTemperatureThr.description: The threshold for the critical Temperature. When temperature exceeds the critical lower temperature, a notification will be sent.

hh3cEntityExtShutdownLowerTemperatureThr.description: The threshold for the shutdown Temperature. When temperature exceeds the lower threshold, a notification will be sent and the entity will be shutdown.

hh3cEntityExtMemSizeRev.name: hh3cEntityExtMemSizeRev

hh3cEntityExtCpuUsageIn1Minute.name: hh3cEntityExtCpuUsageIn1Minute
hh3cEntityExtCpuUsageIn1Minute.description: The CPU usage in last one minute for this entity. Generally, the overall CPU usage on the entity is calculated, independent of the number of CPUs on the entity.

hh3cEntityExtCpuUsageIn5Minutes.name: hh3cEntityExtCpuUsageIn5Minutes
hh3cEntityExtCpuUsageIn5Minutes.description: The CPU usage in last five minutes for this entity. Generally, the overall CPU usage on the entity is calculated, independent of the number of CPUs on the entity.

hh3cEntityExtManuTable.name: hh3cEntityExtManuTable

hh3cEntityExtManuEntry.name: hh3cEntityExtManuEntry
hh3cEntityExtManuEntry.description: The device manufacture information about a particular physical entity.

hh3cEntityExtManuPhysicalIndex.name: hh3cEntityExtManuPhysicalIndex

hh3cEntityExtManuSerialNum.name: hh3cEntityExtManuSerialNum
hh3cEntityExtManuSerialNum.description: Manufacture serial number. The manufacture serial number of the entity such as chassis, module, and so on. It is got from the device when manufacturing. For low level box-device, the manufacture serial number is the device-number of System Control Board(SCB for short), it is written into the SCB directly; for middle level or high level frame-device, the manufacture serial number is the device-numbers of SCB and Service Board, because the SCB, Service Board and chassis are separate to sale and the device-number of chassis cannot be written into board.

hh3cEntityExtManuBuildInfo.description: Device version information. The device version information of the entity such as chassis, module, and so on. It consists of software version information and hardware version information.

hh3cEntityExtManuBOM.name: hh3cEntityExtManuBOM
hh3cEntityExtManuBOM.description: Device BOM code. The device BOM code of the entity such as chassis, module, and so on. It is the component code of ERP system, which can be disassembled from device-number.

hh3cEntityExtMacAddressCount.name: hh3cEntityExtMacAddressCount
hh3cEntityExtMacAddressCount.description: MAC address count. The count of MAC addresses of the entity, such as chassis, module, or port, and so on.

hh3cEntityExtPowerTable.name: hh3cEntityExtPowerTable

hh3cEntityExtPowerEntry.name: hh3cEntityExtPowerEntry

hh3cEntityExtPowerPhysicalIndex.name: hh3cEntityExtPowerPhysicalIndex

hh3cEntityExtNominalPower.name: hh3cEntityExtNominalPower

hh3cEntityExtCurrentPower.name: hh3cEntityExtCurrentPower
hh3cEntityExtCurrentPower.description: The measured usage power of the entity expressed in milliWatts.

hh3cEntityExtAveragePower.name: hh3cEntityExtAveragePower
hh3cEntityExtAveragePower.description: The average power consumed by the entity expressed in milliWatts. Writing a value of zero to this object resets its value to zero. Writing any other value to this object has no effect on its value and an error is returned.

hh3cEntityExtPeakPower.name: hh3cEntityExtPeakPower
hh3cEntityExtPeakPower.description: The peak power consumed by the entity expressed in milliWatts. Writing a value of zero to this object resets its value to zero. Writing any other value to this object has no effect on its value and an error is returned.

hh3cProcessTable.description: The Table describes the information about a particular process, namely a task.

hh3cProcessEntry.name: hh3cProcessEntry
hh3cProcessEntry.description: The information about a particular process, namely a task.

hh3cProcessID.description: This object indicates the identifier of process, namely task ID in system.

hh3cProcessName.name: hh3cProcessName
hh3cProcessName.description: This object indicates the process name.

hh3cProcessUtil5Min.name: hh3cProcessUtil5Min
hh3cProcessUtil5Min.description: This object provides a general idea of how busy a process caused the processor to be over a 5 minute period. The ratio is calculated by the overall CPU usage caused by the process.

hh3cEntityExtMemUsageThresholdNotificati.name: hh3cEntityExtMemUsageThresholdNotification

hh3cEntityExtOperDisabled.name: hh3cEntityExtOperDisabled
hh3cEntityExtOperDisabled.description: The trap indicates the entity is not operable at present.

hh3cEntityExtCriticalTemperatureThreshol.description: The hh3cEntityExtCriticalTemperatureThresholdNotification indicates the temperature exceeds the critical temperature. hh3cEntityExtForcedPowerOn.name: hh3cEntityExtForcedPowerOn

hh3cEntityExtMemAllocatedFailed.name: hh3cEntityExtMemAllocatedFailed

hh3cEntityExtCritLowerTempThresholdNotif.name: hh3cEntityExtCritLowerTempThresholdNotification

hh3cEntityExtSFPInvalidInDays.description: The days when the transceiver module is still valid, but after those days, it will be invalidated.
